{
  "stem": "19969.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 70.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Because the 1st Battalion went right into Munich with very little difficulty.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But on the morning of the 30th, the Germans were shot at that point.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They just weren't putting up any more resistance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So I followed the First Battalion and had them set up a headquarters in the city of Munich.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Oh.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "That morning, on the 30th, I got word that an artillery battalion from the Corps, Corps Army, would come up to relieve me that morning of the 30th.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Well, I had L Company in there so I pulled L Company out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I took L Company in with me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And this Army [INAUDIBLE] battalion commander came up and I explained the situation to him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He took over the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "When I got into Munich and late that evening, I got word that I had to go back and relieve that artillery battalion.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "By that time I'm furious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Well, I said, I'm not going to be in a hurry about it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Well, the next morning-- that would have been on May 1st, I guess-- I sent L Company back there, I went back with them, and when we took over the camp again and were there until May 3rd, when-- L Company was there until May 3rd, when a unit from our division, the 179th Infantry, took over the camp.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Well, that was about it as far as camp was concerned.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The ones I spoke to-- it finally dawned on me after we'd been there a little while that we-- we-- we encountered several prisoners who were outside of a-- of a prison compound and they were in pretty good shape.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it dawned on me these guys were what we might call trustees.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
